<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1788,2030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,225,1788,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">Notes.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krombein" authorityYear="1968" box="[354,466,1788,1814]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Hylomesa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[354,466,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">Hylomesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains 10 species and one subspecies worldwide, among these eight species and one subspecies are distributed in the Oriental Region, one in the Afrotropical Region and one in the Palearctic Region. One species was recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[513,580,1860,1886]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">China</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." box="[623,797,1860,1887]" pageId="2" pageNumber="154" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref17204" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1986) A Contribution to the Knowledge of the Taiwanese Tiphiidae (Hymenoptera, Tiphiidae). Special Publications of the Japan Hymenopterists Association, 33, 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="1986">Tsuneki (1986)</bibRefCitation>
. In this study, four species were collected, including one new species and two new records.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="2" pageNumber="154" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1788,2030]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,150,465]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1932,1958]" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Head more or less square (
<figureCitation box="[733,807,1932,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,183,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hylomesa punctata sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 1. Habitus, dorsal view (CM: marginal cell; CSM I: the first sub mar- ginal cell; CSM II: the second sub marginal cell; CSM III: the third sub marginal cell); 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Vertex, dorsal view; 4. Pronotum, dorsal view; 5. Mesosoma, lateral view; 6. Propodeum, dorsal view; 7. T1, dorsal view; 8. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641316/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[821,851,1932,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[865,895,1932,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[153,1437,479,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-183@6.[151,1437,475,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–24. Hylomesa longiceps, ♀. 16. Habitus, dorsal view; 17. Head, frontal view; 18. Vertex, dorsal view; 19. Prono- tum, dorsal view; 20. Pronotum, lateral view; 21. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 22. Propodeum, dorsal view; 23. T1, dorsal view; 24. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641328/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[908,937,1932,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="154">28</figureCitation>
) in dorsal view; mandible (
<figureCitation box="[1253,1327,1932,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,183,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hylomesa punctata sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 1. Habitus, dorsal view (CM: marginal cell; CSM I: the first sub mar- ginal cell; CSM II: the second sub marginal cell; CSM III: the third sub marginal cell); 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Vertex, dorsal view; 4. Pronotum, dorsal view; 5. Mesosoma, lateral view; 6. Propodeum, dorsal view; 7. T1, dorsal view; 8. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641316/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1341,1370,1932,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[153,1437,479,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-183@6.[151,1437,475,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–24. Hylomesa longiceps, ♀. 16. Habitus, dorsal view; 17. Head, frontal view; 18. Vertex, dorsal view; 19. Prono- tum, dorsal view; 20. Pronotum, lateral view; 21. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 22. Propodeum, dorsal view; 23. T1, dorsal view; 24. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641328/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">17</figureCitation>
) with a stout subapical tooth on inner margin; clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[717,791,1968,1994]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,183,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hylomesa punctata sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 1. Habitus, dorsal view (CM: marginal cell; CSM I: the first sub mar- ginal cell; CSM II: the second sub marginal cell; CSM III: the third sub marginal cell); 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Vertex, dorsal view; 4. Pronotum, dorsal view; 5. Mesosoma, lateral view; 6. Propodeum, dorsal view; 7. T1, dorsal view; 8. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641316/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[805,834,1968,1994]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[153,1437,479,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-183@6.[151,1437,475,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–24. Hylomesa longiceps, ♀. 16. Habitus, dorsal view; 17. Head, frontal view; 18. Vertex, dorsal view; 19. Prono- tum, dorsal view; 20. Pronotum, lateral view; 21. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 22. Propodeum, dorsal view; 23. T1, dorsal view; 24. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641328/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">17</figureCitation>
) with weak to strong median carina; occipital carina complete dorsally; mesosoma (
<figureCitation box="[500,565,2004,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,183,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hylomesa punctata sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 1. Habitus, dorsal view (CM: marginal cell; CSM I: the first sub mar- ginal cell; CSM II: the second sub marginal cell; CSM III: the third sub marginal cell); 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Vertex, dorsal view; 4. Pronotum, dorsal view; 5. Mesosoma, lateral view; 6. Propodeum, dorsal view; 7. T1, dorsal view; 8. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641316/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) considerably longer than wide; pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1135,2004,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,183,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hylomesa punctata sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 1. Habitus, dorsal view (CM: marginal cell; CSM I: the first sub mar- ginal cell; CSM II: the second sub marginal cell; CSM III: the third sub marginal cell); 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Vertex, dorsal view; 4. Pronotum, dorsal view; 5. Mesosoma, lateral view; 6. Propodeum, dorsal view; 7. T1, dorsal view; 8. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641316/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1148,1177,2004,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1189,1219,2004,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[153,1437,479,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-183@6.[151,1437,475,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–24. Hylomesa longiceps, ♀. 16. Habitus, dorsal view; 17. Head, frontal view; 18. Vertex, dorsal view; 19. Prono- tum, dorsal view; 20. Pronotum, lateral view; 21. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 22. Propodeum, dorsal view; 23. T1, dorsal view; 24. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641328/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="154">19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1231,1260,2004,2030]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="154">29</figureCitation>
) comparatively longer than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1890" box="[317,378,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Mesa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[317,378,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Mesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sometimes apically with strongly transverse carina; anterior surface of mesopleuron (
<figureCitation box="[1357,1431,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,183,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hylomesa punctata sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 1. Habitus, dorsal view (CM: marginal cell; CSM I: the first sub mar- ginal cell; CSM II: the second sub marginal cell; CSM III: the third sub marginal cell); 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Vertex, dorsal view; 4. Pronotum, dorsal view; 5. Mesosoma, lateral view; 6. Propodeum, dorsal view; 7. T1, dorsal view; 8. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641316/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,180,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[153,1437,479,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-183@6.[151,1437,475,1880]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–24. Hylomesa longiceps, ♀. 16. Habitus, dorsal view; 17. Head, frontal view; 18. Vertex, dorsal view; 19. Prono- tum, dorsal view; 20. Pronotum, lateral view; 21. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 22. Propodeum, dorsal view; 23. T1, dorsal view; 24. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641328/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="155">20</figureCitation>
) more or less concave; propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[598,672,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,183,1490]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1490]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hylomesa punctata sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 1. Habitus, dorsal view (CM: marginal cell; CSM I: the first sub mar- ginal cell; CSM II: the second sub marginal cell; CSM III: the third sub marginal cell); 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Vertex, dorsal view; 4. Pronotum, dorsal view; 5. Mesosoma, lateral view; 6. Propodeum, dorsal view; 7. T1, dorsal view; 8. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641316/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Figs 6</figureCitation>
, 
