<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,150,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="155">
Male. Head (
<figureCitation box="[349,433,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) not square as in female; clypeus almost same as in female, but median carina weaker; pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[275,356,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) anteriorly strongly carinate; mesopleuron without anterior carina and not produced anteriorly in middle; propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[389,471,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) with carina between dorsal and posterior surfaces; T1 (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1192,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) anteriorly weakly to strongly carinate; inner margin of hind coxa carinate; length of S7 0.4–0.5× less than length of the T7 (
<figureCitation box="[1316,1398,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[152,1432,190,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[151,1435,181,1680]" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Hylomesa taiwana, 25, 28–29, 31, 33, 35, ♀; 26–27, 30, 32, 34, 36, ♂. 25–26. Habitus, dorsal view; 27. Head, ventral view; 28. Vertex, dorsal view; 29–30. Pronotum, dorsal view; 31–32. Propodeum, dorsal view; 33–34. T1, dorsal view; 35. T6, dorsal view; 36. T7, lateral view." pageId="3" pageNumber="155">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) in lateral view.
</paragraph>
